NAME:
   makedir - Creates a new directory
 
SYNOPSIS:
   makedir [NEW_DIRECTORY_NAME]
 
DESCRIPTION:
    Creates a new directory with one or more names/paths of the parameter introduced 

   Optional arguments:

   -v : Prints if the directory has been created or if it already exists
   -m : Allows the user to add specific permissions.
    
SEE ALSO:
   cd(1P), cp(1), pwd(1)
 
REPORTING BUGS:
   Write down here error that you have detected in your program and you can not correct. For example if you can not guarantee the answer when the argument is a number.
   Do not support the double minus options for now.
 
AUTHORS:
